    "In Fig. 4, we plot the prediction behavior of our finetuned reward models.",
    "We can see that as inputs to the models become increasingly unfamiliar, model predictions indeed default toward P unf (y).",
    "This experiment illustrates that, depending on their finetuning data, reward models can generate different kinds of hallucinations, which can have different downstream effects when providing reward supervision for RL finetuning.",
